caption: Food was very good and service as good as can be expected in the time of covid.
The cafe_dewitt instagram has the daily specials and amazing pics for their delicious foods.  The food is always great.
Food was really good! Staff was extremely nice! Everything was very clean and social distant. Def recommend.
Really friendly service with great food. The otherwise meh space is brightened with well maintained aquaria and staff excited to tell you about the fish.

Safe during Covid times AND the food is delicious, we ate the Zoe salad, omelette and brioche and all were exquisite.  If you’re in the area I definitely recommend taking a takeout or dining in safely.  Design isn’t very inviting but the food and service are! :)

Great cafe! Handled Covid restrictions well! Delicious pulled pork sandwich and taco special! Friendly Chef and waiter. Gave us recommendations for local wineries and breweries. High quality ingredients used at a reasonable price!
A little too expensive for what you get but nice staff !

I worked here as a waitress for a year, and I cannot recommend it enough, both as an employee AND as a customer. The food is great, the people are great, the atmosphere? Shocker: also great. I am an Ithaca native, and I can promise you that …
Go to brunch place in Ithaca, especially for an omelette. Love choosing from their specials.
While the atmosphere is, well, there IS no atmosphere as mall guests walk between the tables in the seating area, the food is good and the staff is awesome!
Egg-cellent omelettes! ;) cute atmosphere with very tasty food and great service. Staff was attentive and the locally sourced food made a difference!
Great food, but wait for too long.

Amazing food and good quantity! Loved the Brioche French Toast there, do try it. The only caveat is that it is a cash only place so do carry cash with you before you go there although there is an ATM in the building!

Our go-to breakfast spot in Ithaca. If you like french toast, get it here and prepare to have your mind blown. Friendly staff in a cute area full of Ithaca characters. I've never had lunch here, but if it is half as good as the breakfast you should be fine.

The food was good, but the prices were ridiculous. I ordered 2 eggs, 1 sausage link, and toast. The total was $11.50: $4.50 for the eggs (what? I can buy a carton of eggs for that much), $4.50 for a SINGLE sausage link, $2.50 for a baguette slice that’s cut in half. That is absurd. Someone explain. Not correct. Goodbye.
Tasty food , bit pricey and good service.  FYI They only take CASH !!!

Had a delicious brunch with friends on a Sunday morning. Staff was fantastic and attentive. Food was excellent and fast. We had a group six and everything was spot on! I ordered the pecan waffle special. This waffle was wonderful...made …
Always delicious local ingredients and casual but good service.
Pleasant staff and good food. Well priced. The building and space feels a bit out-dated but it's a good spot to check out.
Food was good, service a bit slow, they seemed pretty busy.
One of Our favorite places for breakfast . Friendly, personable service every time
(Translated by Google) Super addictive lunch.  (Original) Súper adictivo almuerzo.
I love their Jam! Omggg.
Friendly staff and great food.

OMG!! Lived in this area over 30yrs and never ate here! Took an out of town friend to discover this hidden jem. FYI go on Tuesday for the burger of all burgers!! Sure NYC and Portland D.C. etc have great food but don't forget the folks …
Good food, other than the specials the menu has remained the same for at least 5 years. There's something for everyone. Cash only.
Great food.
Best coffee and brunch in Ithaca
Love their french onion soup
Good service and food is ok, but nothing special
Great meal and wonderful staff. Everything you would how for from Ithaca.
Always delicious food, sometimes severs are busy enough to confuse orders/service.
Adorable ❤️
One of the best little brunches in Ithaca. Great, well-prepared breakfasts and generously porportioned sandwiches. CASH ONLY. Awesome staff and lovely atmosphere. Go, you won't be disappointed
Very good inside cafe.
The food coffee was great. Service was excellent. The atmosphere was community oriented and inviting.
My favorite breakfast/brunch place! Everything is made with local ingredients and they make a lot of baked goods, condiments, etc in house, which I love!
Service is friendly but slow.  Food is good.  Location is not the greatest if the mall is busy.
Special food, special space, special shops! Only in Ithaca! What a place! And Goldfish too!👍
They are always friendly and nice to everyone. Food is great too 🙂 i love how they cooked the potato so much.
Good food, but the service was slow and cash only.
Only takes cash and checks! Be prepared

I was a bit disappointed with my meal here. I used to frequent Café DeWitt because it was consistently good. This last time I ate here Iordered a special sandwich on the blackboard. I thought the sandwich was flavorless. My friend felt the …
Always fantastic food!
While the food was great, it took over an hour for our food to come out. Staff seemed unbothered by our complaint.

The food here is great. The morning glory sandwich is my absolute favorite breakfast sandwich anywhere. But the last 2 times Ive gone the service has been poor. While not very busy  either time we ended up waiting nearly an hour for our …
Food was excellent. A bit pricy.

This place is AMAZING! Aside from the fact that you most probably have to wait for a long time during weekends, it's perfect. The atmosphere is pleasant; crowdy yet cozy. The staffs are very friendly and polite. And of course, the food--- …
One of my top breakfast choices in town. Breakfast sandwich always a go-to, some of the best pancakes in Ithaca, and Omelette specials always great. Nice work Dewitt Crew.

I eat here about once a week. I love the wait staff, and have never had a meal I dislike. They have big fish tanks all around one side of the cafe which somehow makes up for the fact that there are no windows. I never feel closed in, and since the mall hallway runs through it, it is a great place to see and be seen.
Excellent Breakfast, Brunch, and Lunch spot. Great menu that changes daily. Cash only.

Deliciousness, I've had several brunches here and the food was fanominal.  The atmosphere is busy but cosy. It is truly unique, how having the distractions of passerbys, brings, your focus more on your food and the people with whom you are sharing it with.
The food is always well prepared and tasty. At times the service can be lackluster, but that really varies.

Perfect breakfast! Locally sourced, fresh and quick. We both had specials. I had avocado toast with fried eggs ( instead of scrambled) and ordered a side of basil hazelnut pesto. DH had a breakfast sandwich with roasted potatoes that he …
Slow service and does not accept credit cards! Food is average.

I live right nearby and love their service and locally-sourced food. Food is good, selection nothing too amazing, but just really solid. Free coffee refills are a plus! It's no wonder there's always a huge line during weekends. Staff are friendly, though service is not very fast. Plan for a little extra time to finish up a meal here.
The fried egg sandwich is divine.  The coffee is weak, recommend drinking more than you're used to.

I was here with my girlfriend on breakfast, when we were traveling through Ithaca, and we had a great time in this restaurant. The breakfast was delicious, served quickly and the price was reasonable. Their staff is professional, polite and …

Wonderful gluten free options. This place is a little hidden away in Dewitt Mall. The surroundings are clean, but basic. As soon as you put a bit of chutney in your mouth, every else fades away and you forget where you even are. The taste …
Good food, decent prices, good service.

We came here for brunch on a Saturday. Free street parking right outside. There was about a 4 minute wait to get seated and about 30 to get our food. Highly recommend the omelette carol and the fresh squeezed orange juicy. Cozy little spot that serves organic and locally grown foods. Delicious!

Great food. Interesting space. Nice servers. They lost a star for slower service (especially waiting for a check) and not being able to read the specials on the chalk board. Someone needs better penmanship. And cash only?
Took a while to get served, but the food was delicious. Worth the wait.

We must have arrived at the right time.  No wait, fast service and the waiter was very efficient and courteous.  The food was wonderful.  Yummy, unique, very fresh and presented well.  The only knock (and not that big of a deal considering the area) was the price of our breakfast was a bit over the top (about $15/per person).

Cash only? It's 2017, how has this place not discovered Square readers? Wobbly tables, incomplete menu, slow service, super slow kitchen. They've had these problems for years and seem uninterested in making improvements. Good food but save yourself the hassle.
One of the best places to get breakfast in Ithaca, in my opinion.

Great food, long wait. Each time I've been here, there is a 30-45 minute wait, and ordering takes another 45 minutes until food arrives on your plate. When it does come, however, it's really great. I like to come here when I'm with a friend …

The "Apple Sausage and Potato Hash" was fantastic!! Can't wait to return for more. Great food with good service. Don't expect the huge plates heaping with food you find at diners, but if you want excellent food with local ingredients this is the place to go. Superb spot for a light brunch.

Great breakfast and lunch spot with a special brunch menu on the weekends. It gets very busy on the weekends so expect a wait, but it's worth it. Awesome staff, interesting location in a historic building. Try the morning glory sandwich, which you can get with avocado instead of bacon
Great location for brunch

Probably my favorite brunch place in Ithaca. Everything is local and all natural. Love the huevos rancheros. Careful though, they run out of ingredients quick due to the high demand so get there early.
Some of the best food in Ithaca!
(Translated by Google) I found the coffee very good.  (Original) Eu achei muito bom o café.
